{"type":"message","id":"27da1005","parentId":"d2b92438","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:33:48.372Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the config.js uses `socketPath` from `DB_SOCKET` env var, and it falls back to the XAMPP socket path. My .env file doesn't set `DB_SOCKET`, so it's using the XAMPP path. I need to either:\n1. Set `DB_SOCKET` to empty or not set in .env (but it defaults to the XAMPP path)\n2. Actually, looking at the code, if `DB_SOCKET` is not set, it uses the XAMPP path. But in MySQL2, when `socketPath` is provided, it uses the socket; when not provided, it uses host:port.\n\n\nThe issue is that `socketPath` defaults to the XAMPP path, so I need to explicitly set `DB_SOCKET=` to empty in my .env to let MySQL2 use the host/port connection instead. I'll update the .env file and try connecting via host and port rather than the socket.","thinkingSignature":"bdf2ecde50b8b7bc05763dfdb87709dd7ecfca7bcae1fada81f85c27aa5df769"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gf11cxqbhi5c_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/apps/codexpool/.env","newText":"DB_HOST=127.0.0.1\nDB_PORT=3306\nDB_SOCKET=","oldText":"DB_HOST=127.0.0.1\nDB_PORT=3306"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11601,"output":300,"cacheRead":24939,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36840,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774085620464}}
