{"type":"message","id":"ddddb17c","parentId":"176852de","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:33:51.936Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"But wait, the issue is that `socketPath` is set to `process.env.DB_SOCKET || '/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/var/mysql/mysql.sock'`. If I set `DB_SOCKET=` to empty string, `process.env.DB_SOCKET` will be `''` (empty string), which is falsy, so it will still fall back to the XAMPP path.\n\nI need to modify the config.js or find another way. Actually, the cleanest fix is to just modify the config.js to not use socketPath when it's empty.Let me look at db.js to understand how it uses the socket.","thinkingSignature":"264e8a10a8575a02276eef5fc410184b73c62a32229134f1adb57fd81b5d04f6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f68dombwproo_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/apps/codexpool/server/db.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11936,"output":174,"cacheRead":24939,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37049,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774085628414}}
