{"type":"message","id":"3a42b57c","parentId":"b7c0465c","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:51:16.509Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me implement both features:1. z-score scoring: Replace rank percentile with z-score standardization\n2. Multi-indicator market breadth: Add trend + Macd to the existing MA20 breadthFor z-score scoring:\n- Instead of using `rank(pct=True)`, use `(x - mean) / std`\n- For mean reversion factors (dist_ma10, ret5, excess_ret5), the more negative, the better\n- So z-score of these should be computed and then we use -z for scoring (more negative = better = higher score)For market breadth upgrade:\n- Current: just `(close > ma20).mean()` \n\n\n- New: combine 3 indicators with weighted average","thinkingSignature":"b775cacdd300f3caca047901e902d5c8c4da8e10d3c6066f34df5137fe93aec3"},{"type":"text","text":"现在同步实现两个功能。先看现有 compute_features_for_date 完整逻辑：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r659fnigh24m_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_day1_3_mean_reversion_signals.py","offset":1,"limit":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56204,"output":238,"cacheRead":24939,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81381,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774086668981}}
{"type":"message","id":"80d9e985","parentId":"3a42b57c","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:51:16.550Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r659fnigh24m_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Generate day1-3 style mean reversion signals.\n\nSimplified version: compute features directly for target date.\n\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport yaml\n\nPROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nDEFAULT_CONFIG = PROJECT_ROOT / \"config\" / \"day1_3_mean_reversion.yaml\"\n\n\ndef load_yaml(path: Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    data = yaml.safe_load(path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    return data or {}\n\n\ndef normalize_ts_code(raw: str) -> str:\n    s = raw.strip().upper()\n    if not s or s == \"NAN\":\n        return \"\"\n    if s.endswith((\".SH\", \".SZ\", \".BJ\")):\n        return s\n    if s.startswith((\"60\", \"68\", \"90\")):\n        return f\"{s}.SH\"\n    if s.startswith((\"00\", \"30\")):\n        return f\"{s}.SZ\"\n    if s.startswith((\"4\", \"8\")):\n        return f\"{s}.BJ\"\n    return s\n\n\ndef load_history(path: Path, target_date: str, lookback_days: int = 120) -> pd.DataFrame:\n    \"\"\"Load history from cutoff date.\"\"\"\n    cutoff_date = str(int(target_date.replace(\"-\", \"\")) - lookback_days * 100)  # rough estimate\n    \n    chunks = []\n    for chunk in pd.read_csv(path, chunksize=500000, dtype={\"trade_date\": str}):\n        chunk = chunk[chunk[\"trade_date\"] >= cutoff_date]\n        if not chunk.empty:\n            chunks.append(chunk)\n    \n    if not chunks:\n        raise ValueError(f\"No data after cutoff {cutoff_date}\")\n    \n    df = pd.concat(chunks, ignore_index=True)\n    df[\"ts_code\"] = df[\"ts_code\"].map(normalize_ts_code)\n    df[\"trade_date\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\"trade_date\"], format=\"%Y%m%d\", errors=\"coerce\")\n    return df.dropna(subset=[\"trade_date\", \"ts_code\", \"close\"]).sort_values([\"ts_code\", \"trade_date\"])\n\n\ndef compute_features_for_date(df: pd.DataFrame, target_date: str, index_df: pd.DataFrame = None) -> pd.DataFrame:\n\n[284 more lines in file. Use offset=61 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774086676538}}
{"type":"message","id":"366ca067","parentId":"80d9e985","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:51:20.039Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the full compute_features_for_date and compute_market_gate functions:","thinkingSignature":"d4cfff948ef06f2e531732f84b7a27aeae2be0aeb4330993c214b7a7a52116a1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9yokwrzddi1b_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_day1_3_mean_reversion_signals.py","offset":61,"limit":100}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":56973,"output":93,"cacheRead":24939,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82005,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774086676552}}
{"type":"message","id":"10795b4a","parentId":"366ca067","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:51:20.076Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9yokwrzddi1b_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    \"\"\"Compute technical features for a specific date.\"\"\"\n    trade_date = pd.to_datetime(target_date)\n    \n    # Get latest date data\n    latest = df[df[\"trade_date\"] == trade_date].copy()\n    if len(latest) == 0:\n        # Try previous date\n        dates = df[\"trade_date\"].drop_duplicates().sort_values()\n        trade_date = dates.iloc[-1]\n        latest = df[df[\"trade_date\"] == trade_date].copy()\n        print(f\"Using previous date: {trade_date}\")\n    \n    # Compute rolling features on FULL history, then filter to latest date\n    # This ensures we have enough history for rolling calculations\n    g = df.groupby(\"ts_code\", group_keys=False)\n    df[\"ma10\"] = g[\"close\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(10, min_periods=5).mean())\n    df[\"ma20\"] = g[\"close\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean())\n    df[\"hh20\"] = g[\"high\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(20, min_periods=10).max())\n    df[\"ll20\"] = g[\"low\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(20, min_periods=10).min())\n    \n    # Get latest date features after rolling is computed\n    latest = df[df[\"trade_date\"] == trade_date].copy()\n    \n    # Compute ret5 using pivot on recent data\n    recent = df[df[\"trade_date\"] <= trade_date].groupby(\"ts_code\").tail(6).sort_values([\"ts_code\", \"trade_date\"])\n    piv = recent.pivot(index=\"trade_date\", columns=\"ts_code\", values=\"close\")\n    if len(piv) >= 6:\n        ret5 = (piv.iloc[-1] / piv.iloc[-6] - 1).to_dict()\n        latest[\"ret5\"] = latest[\"ts_code\"].map(ret5)\n    else:\n        latest[\"ret5\"] = np.nan\n\n    # Compute amount_ma5 and amount_ma20 for volume trend filter\n    amt_recent = df[df[\"trade_date\"] <= trade_date].groupby(\"ts_code\").tail(25).sort_values([\"ts_code\", \"trade_date\"])\n    g_amt = amt_recent.groupby(\"ts_code\", group_keys=False)\n    amt_recent[\"amt_ma5\"] = g_amt[\"amount\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(5, min_periods=3).mean())\n    amt_recent[\"amt_ma20\"] = g_amt[\"amount\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean())\n    amt_latest = amt_recent[amt_recent[\"trade_date\"] == trade_date][[\"ts_code\", \"amt_ma5\", \"amt_ma20\"]].copy()\n    latest = latest.merge(amt_latest, on=\"ts_code\", how=\"left\")\n    latest[\"amount_ratio\"] = (latest[\"amt_ma5\"] / latest[\"amt_ma20\"].replace(0, np.nan)).clip(lower=0).fillna(1.0)\n    \n    # Compute excess_ret5 relative to HS300 index\n    if index_df is not None:\n        idx = index_df[index_df[\"date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n        if len(idx) >= 6:\n            idx = idx.sort_values(\"date\").tail(6)\n            hs300_ret5 = float(idx[\"close\"].iloc[-1] / idx[\"close\"].iloc[0] - 1)\n            latest[\"excess_ret5\"] = latest[\"ret5\"].fillna(0) - hs300_ret5\n        else:\n            latest[\"excess_ret5\"] = 0.0\n    else:\n        latest[\"excess_ret5\"] = 0.0\n    \n    # Derived features\n    latest[\"dist_ma10\"] = (latest[\"close\"] / latest[\"ma10\"] - 1.0).fillna(0)\n    rng = (latest[\"hh20\"] - latest[\"ll20\"]).replace(0, np.nan)\n    latest[\"range_pos20\"] = ((latest[\"close\"] - latest[\"ll20\"]) / rng).clip(0, 1).fillna(0.5)\n    latest[\"reversal_bar\"] = ((latest[\"close\"] - latest[\"open\"]) / latest[\"open\"].replace(0, np.nan)).fillna(0)\n    \n    return latest, trade_date\n\n\ndef compute_market_gate(index_df: pd.DataFrame, history_df: pd.DataFrame, trade_date: pd.Timestamp, cfg: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute market regime with real breadth calculation.\"\"\"\n    # Get index trend\n    idx = index_df[index_df[\"date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    if len(idx) < 20:\n        return {\"regime\": \"neutral\", \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": 0.0, \"scale\": 0.6}\n    \n    idx[\"ma20\"] = idx[\"close\"].rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean()\n    latest_idx = idx.iloc[-1]\n    trend = float(latest_idx[\"close\"] / latest_idx[\"ma20\"] - 1.0) if pd.notna(latest_idx[\"ma20\"]) else 0.0\n    \n    # Compute REAL market breadth: % of stocks above their 20-day MA\n    # First compute MA20 for all stocks up to trade_date\n    hist = history_df[history_df[\"trade_date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    g = hist.groupby(\"ts_code\", group_keys=False)\n    hist[\"ma20_stock\"] = g[\"close\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean())\n    \n    # Get latest date data\n    latest = hist[hist[\"trade_date\"] == trade_date].copy()\n    latest = latest.dropna(subset=[\"ma20_stock\"])\n    \n    if len(latest) >= 50:  # Need enough stocks for meaningful breadth\n        breadth = float((latest[\"close\"] > latest[\"ma20_stock\"]).mean())\n    else:\n        breadth = 0.5  # Default if not enough data\n    \n    strong_breadth = cfg.get(\"strong_breadth\", 0.58)\n    neutral_breadth = cfg.get(\"neutral_breadth\", 0.48)\n    weak_floor = cfg.get(\"weak_index_trend_floor\", -0.03)\n    \n    # Determine regime based on BOTH trend AND breadth\n    if breadth >= strong_breadth and trend >= 0:\n        regime, scale = \"strong\", cfg.get(\"strong_scale\", 1.0)\n    elif breadth >= neutral_breadth and trend >= weak_floor:\n        regime, scale = \"neutral\", cfg.get(\"neutral_scale\", 0.6)\n    else:\n        regime, scale = \"weak\", cfg.get(\"weak_scale\", 0.3)\n    \n\n[184 more lines in file. Use offset=161 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774086680063}}
{"type":"message","id":"63c84ecc","parentId":"10795b4a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:51:52.644Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full structure. Let me implement:\n\n1. **Z-score scoring**: Replace rank percentile with z-score normalization\n2. **Multi-indicator market breadth**: Add MACD histogram + trend composite\n\nFor z-score:\n- `z = (x - mean) / std` for each factor\n- For mean reversion factors (dist_ma10, ret5, excess_ret5, range_pos20): more negative = better\n- So we negate the z-score: `score_component = -z` (more negative original → higher score)\n- For reversal_bar: higher = better, so `score_component = z`\n\n\n- Now I'm updating the compute_market_gate function to incorporate MACD histogram alongside the existing trend and breadth indicators, then normalizing the combined score to determine the market regime.","thinkingSignature":"d1924658843a189dfc655cd60df3232c0adcddb51e958ad9930f29314ae5ff9a"},{"type":"text","text":"现在实现两项增强。先更新 compute_market_gate 加入 MACD：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ifxdeyd4cg37_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/generate_day1_3_mean_reversion_signals.py","oldText":"def compute_market_gate(index_df: pd.DataFrame, history_df: pd.DataFrame, trade_date: pd.Timestamp, cfg: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute market regime with real breadth calculation.\"\"\"\n    # Get index trend\n    idx = index_df[index_df[\"date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    if len(idx) < 20:\n        return {\"regime\": \"neutral\", \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": 0.0, \"scale\": 0.6}\n    \n    idx[\"ma20\"] = idx[\"close\"].rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean()\n    latest_idx = idx.iloc[-1]\n    trend = float(latest_idx[\"close\"] / latest_idx[\"ma20\"] - 1.0) if pd.notna(latest_idx[\"ma20\"]) else 0.0\n    \n    # Compute REAL market breadth: % of stocks above their 20-day MA\n    # First compute MA20 for all stocks up to trade_date\n    hist = history_df[history_df[\"trade_date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    g = hist.groupby(\"ts_code\", group_keys=False)\n    hist[\"ma20_stock\"] = g[\"close\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean())\n    \n    # Get latest date data\n    latest = hist[hist[\"trade_date\"] == trade_date].copy()\n    latest = latest.dropna(subset=[\"ma20_stock\"])\n    \n    if len(latest) >= 50:  # Need enough stocks for meaningful breadth\n        breadth = float((latest[\"close\"] > latest[\"ma20_stock\"]).mean())\n    else:\n        breadth = 0.5  # Default if not enough data\n    \n    strong_breadth = cfg.get(\"strong_breadth\", 0.58)\n    neutral_breadth = cfg.get(\"neutral_breadth\", 0.48)\n    weak_floor = cfg.get(\"weak_index_trend_floor\", -0.03)\n    \n    # Determine regime based on BOTH trend AND breadth\n    if breadth >= strong_breadth and trend >= 0:\n        regime, scale = \"strong\", cfg.get(\"strong_scale\", 1.0)\n    elif breadth >= neutral_breadth and trend >= weak_floor:\n        regime, scale = \"neutral\", cfg.get(\"neutral_scale\", 0.6)\n    else:\n        regime, scale = \"weak\", cfg.get(\"weak_scale\", 0.3)\n    \n    return {\"regime\": regime, \"breadth\": round(breadth, 4), \"trend\": round(trend, 4), \"scale\": scale}","new_string":"def zscore(series: pd.Series) -> pd.Series:\n    \"\"\"Z-score standardization (handle constant/std=0 edge case).\"\"\"\n    mean = series.mean()\n    std = series.std()\n    if std == 0 or np.isnan(std):\n        return pd.Series(0.0, index=series.index)\n    return (series - mean) / std\n\n\ndef compute_market_gate(index_df: pd.DataFrame, history_df: pd.DataFrame, trade_date: pd.Timestamp, cfg: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute market regime with multi-indicator breadth (MA20 breadth + trend + MACD).\"\"\"\n    # Get index history\n    idx = index_df[index_df[\"date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    if len(idx) < 20:\n        return {\"regime\": \"neutral\", \"breadth\": 0.5, \"trend\": 0.0, \"scale\": 0.6}\n\n    # Indicator 1: Index trend vs MA20\n    idx[\"ma20\"] = idx[\"close\"].rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean()\n    latest_idx = idx.iloc[-1]\n    trend = float(latest_idx[\"close\"] / latest_idx[\"ma20\"] - 1.0) if pd.notna(latest_idx[\"ma20\"]) else 0.0\n\n    # Indicator 2: MA20 breadth (% of stocks above their 20-day MA)\n    hist = history_df[history_df[\"trade_date\"] <= trade_date].copy()\n    g = hist.groupby(\"ts_code\", group_keys=False)\n    hist[\"ma20_stock\"] = g[\"close\"].transform(lambda s: s.rolling(20, min_periods=10).mean())\n    latest = hist[hist[\"trade_date\"] == trade_date].copy().dropna(subset=[\"ma20_stock\"])\n    breadth = float((latest[\"close\"] > latest[\"ma20_stock\"]).mean()) if len(latest) >= 50 else 0.5\n\n    # Indicator 3: MACD histogram (12/26/9 EMA on index)\n    idx_sorted = idx.sort_values(\"date\")\n    ema12 = idx_sorted[\"close\"].ewm(span=12, adjust=False).mean()\n    ema26 = idx_sorted[\"close\"].ewm(span=26, adjust=False).mean()\n    macd_hist = (ema12 - ema26).ewm(span=9, adjust=False).mean()\n    macd_hist_latest = macd_hist.iloc[-1]\n    macd_signal = 1 if macd_hist_latest > 0 else -1  # 1=bullish, -1=bearish\n\n    # Composite: normalize each to [0,1] then average\n    # trend: normalize around 0 (negative=weak, positive=strong)\n    trend_norm = (trend + 0.05) / 0.10  # -5% to +5% maps to ~[0,1]\n    trend_norm = float(np.clip(trend_norm, 0, 1))\n    breadth_norm = float(np.clip(breadth, 0, 1))\n    macd_norm = 1.0 if macd_signal > 0 else 0.0\n    composite = 0.45 * breadth_norm + 0.30 * trend_norm + 0.25 * macd_norm\n\n    strong_breadth = cfg.get(\"strong_breadth\", 0.58)\n    neutral_breadth = cfg.get(\"neutral_breadth\", 0.48)\n    weak_floor = cfg.get(\"weak_index_trend_floor\", -0.03)\n\n    # Determine regime: use composite + trend floor\n    if composite >= strong_breadth and trend >= 0:\n        regime, scale = \"strong\", cfg.get(\"strong_scale\", 1.0)\n    elif composite >= neutral_breadth and trend >= weak_floor:\n        regime, scale = \"neutral\", cfg.get(\"neutral_scale\", 0.6)\n    else:\n        regime, scale = \"weak\", cfg.get(\"weak_scale\", 0.3)\n\n    return {\n        \"regime\": regime,\n        \"breadth\": round(breadth, 4),\n        \"trend\": round(trend, 4),\n        \"macd\": macd_signal,\n        \"composite\": round(composite, 4),\n        \"scale\": scale\n    }"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58574,"output":1745,"cacheRead":24939,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85258,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774086680079}}
