{"type":"message","id":"ec8c7c4e","parentId":"fe380e11","timestamp":"2026-03-21T09:53:33.565Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"But wait, I also need to make sure the hist_full groupby doesn't cause issues since it's grouped BEFORE the date filter. The rolling computation should be fine because it's computed per ts_code group on the full history.\n\nActually, there's another issue: `history_df` in compute_market_gate already has the ma10/ma20/stock-specific rolling computed. But the `hist[\"ma20_stock\"]` I'm computing here is a separate computation on the full history. This should be fine.\n\nBut wait, I should double check that the hist_full groupby doesn't cause the same problem. When we do `hist_full.groupby(\"ts_code\", group_keys=False)[\"close\"].transform(rolling)`, it computes rolling per stock on the full history. \n\nThe rolling windows are calculated correctly since the data is sorted by ts_code and trade_date, so each stock's 20-day window only looks back within its own group. Let me run this again.","thinkingSignature":"a0c9082214ae56d9ec9b68676951edcec98d3cc3c98e2856d80e25ce3f25b65e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vmfy8gk7edu7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 scripts/generate_day1_3_mean_reversion_signals.py --config config/day1_3_mean_reversion.yaml --trade-date 2026-03-10 2>&1","yieldMs":55000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65394,"output":300,"cacheRead":24939,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90633,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774086806607}}
