{"type":"message","id":"2147fbb9","parentId":"14169e53","timestamp":"2026-03-21T14:53:20.547Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so:\n1. `agents.defaults.sandbox` doesn't exist - I need to add it\n2. `simple` agent doesn't have `sandbox` config - it was mentioned in the audit as `sandbox=off` (since agents.defaults has no sandbox entry, default is off)\n3. `channels.feishu.tools.doc = true` - needs to be set to false for P3\n\nFor P0 - gemma3 web tools: I need to find where tools are configured. Let me check if there's a top-level tools section or if it needs to be added.\n\nFor P1 - sandbox require: I need to add `agents.defaults.sandbox.mode = \"require\"` so all agents need explicit sandbox authorization.\n\n\nNow I need to verify whether a `tools` section already exists in the config or if I need to create one from scratch.","thinkingSignature":"4690b757f55efcc3e7b22505d5270155e6d7e6126c4a07fee674f863905c43d5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7w2ixi1mn5r9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\ncfg = json.load(open('/Users/ling/.openclaw/openclaw.json'))\n# Check top-level keys\nprint('Top-level keys:', list(cfg.keys()))\n# Check for tools deny config\nif 'tools' in cfg:\n    print('tools config exists:', json.dumps(cfg['tools'], indent=2)[:1500])\nelse:\n    print('No tools top-level config')\n# Check openclaw-lark in installs\ninstalls = cfg.get('plugins', {}).get('installs', {})\nif 'openclaw-lark' in installs:\n    print('openclaw-lark install:', json.dumps(installs['openclaw-lark'], indent=2))\n# Check agents.defaults for anything sandbox-related\nprint('agents.defaults keys:', list(cfg.get('agents', {}).get('defaults', {}).keys()))\n\" 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93724,"output":397,"cacheRead":43165,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":137286,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"