{"type":"message","id":"f4f39626","parentId":"caea478f","timestamp":"2026-03-21T14:53:58.904Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `require` mode is not valid. Let me check what the valid values are: \"off\", \"non-main\", \"all\". \n\n\"require\" is not a valid option. Let me think about what the audit actually recommends:\n\nThe audit says: \"enable sandboxing for all sessions (agents.defaults.sandbox.mode=\"all\")\"\n\nBut that might be too restrictive - if I set `mode=\"all\"`, all exec calls will be sandboxed unless explicitly opted out. This could break things.\n\nWait, looking at the error: `allowed: \"off\", \"non-main\", \"all\"`. So the valid values are:\n\n\n- \"off\" - no sandboxing\n- \"non-main\" - sandbox everything except main agent\n- \"all\" - sandbox everything including main\n\nThe audit recommended `mode=\"all\"` for the sandbox setting, but I realize I was confusing this with a different config path. The actual issue was about the small model vulnerability, which needs `sandbox=\"all\"` on the specific agent, not the global defaults.\n\nI could use `non-main` to sandbox everything except the main agent, but that doesn't solve the problem since the small model is the `simple` agent, not `main`. Let me try applying `sandbox.mode=\"all\"` directly to the simple agent instead.","thinkingSignature":"29fac2da157d9f3d2dea7e867f691c5375926f5a69bd0a6b93b1cd26ca481304"},{"type":"text","text":"`sandbox.mode=\"require\"` 不在白名单里，改用有效值 `\"all\"`。同时撤销 P1 改法：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l50ff71ww6wj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport json\n\ncfg = json.load(open('/Users/ling/.openclaw/openclaw.json'))\n\n# P1: Remove the invalid \"require\" from agents.defaults\nif 'sandbox' in cfg['agents']['defaults']:\n    del cfg['agents']['defaults']['sandbox']\n\n# Instead, apply sandbox=all to the simple agent (gemma3)\nfor a in cfg['agents']['list']:\n    if a['id'] == 'simple':\n    