{"type":"message","id":"bf211748","parentId":"e1205231","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:29:31.429Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-21 23:29:30 GMT+8] Feishu[feishu-assistant] DM | ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7 [msg:om_x100b54dfdb687ca8c4abbfc95395386]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54dfdb687ca8c4abbfc95395386\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 23:29 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\"\n}\n```\n\n你读一下https://github.com/heyuqiu2023/CodexPool这个仓库的文档，告诉我怎么使用这个仓库的相关功能"}],"timestamp":1774106971425}}
{"type":"message","id":"4953a7b7","parentId":"bf211748","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:29:43.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to read the CodexPool repository documentation. Let me fetch the README from the repository.","thinkingSignature":"cba2de3564ea4c0438d27fb1bb66e545dffe8ff70231ff99a4a89f488c0a1ed1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_or232yjqrg78_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -sL --max-time 15 \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/heyuqiu2023/CodexPool/main/README.md\" 2>&1","yieldMs":14000,"timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_or232yjqrg78_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -sL --max-time 10 \"https://api.github.com/repos/heyuqiu2023/CodexPool/contents\" | python3 -c \"import sys,json; items=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(i['name'],i['type']) for i in items]\" 2>&1","timeout":12}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":125,"output":196,"cacheRead":133330,"cacheWrite":3826,"totalTokens":137477,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774106971428}}
{"type":"message","id":"62ce0ea5","parentId":"4953a7b7","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:29:43.899Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_or232yjqrg78_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Codex Account Manager\n\nA dashboard for managing multiple OpenAI Codex accounts (ChatGPT OAuth), with real-time usage monitoring and automatic account rotation.\n> 原则上也可用于 Gemini / Claude 等账号管理，但我主要用 Codex，所以示例与实现以 Codex 为主。\n\n\n![Dashboard Preview](public/preview.png)\n\n## Features\n\n- **Multi-account management** — Add and switch between multiple OpenAI Codex accounts using ChatGPT OAuth tokens\n- **Real-time usage monitoring** — Shows 5-hour window and weekly quota usage by calling the Codex API directly\n- **Auto-rotation** — Automatically switches to the next account when the 5-hour usage exceeds 90%\n- **Smart polling** — Adjusts check frequency based on usage level (30min → 10min → 5min as usage increases)\n- **Auth file switching** — Copies the selected account's `auth.json` to `~/.codex/auth.json` on activation\n- **Token info** — Displays email, plan type, and token expiry decoded from JWT\n- **Activity logs** — Real-time log feed with rotation events and usage checks\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Frontend**: React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui\n- **Backend**: Express.js + Node.js\n- **Database**: MySQL (via XAMPP)\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Node.js 18+\n- MySQL (XAMPP recommended on macOS)\n- OpenAI Codex CLI installed (`npm install -g @openai/codex`)\n- ChatGPT Plus / Team / Pro account with Codex access\n\n## Setup\n\n### 1. Clone the repo\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/codex-account-manager.git\ncd codex-account-manager\n```\n\n### 2. Install dependencies\n\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n\n### 3. Configure environment\n\n```bash\ncp .env.example .env\n```\n\nEdit `.env` with your database credentials:\n\n```env\nPORT=3001\nFRONTEND_ORIGIN=http://localhost:8080\nDB_HOST=127.0.0.1\nDB_PORT=3306\nDB_SOCKET=/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/var/mysql/mysql.sock\nDB_USER=root\nDB_PASSWORD=\nDB_NAME=codex_pool_manager\nVITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001\n```\n\n### 4. Create the database\n\nStart MySQL, then create a database named `codex_pool_manager`. The server will auto-create all tables on first run.\n\n### 5. Start the app\n\n```bash\n# Start backend\nnode server/index.js\n\n# Start frontend (in another terminal)\nnpm run dev\n```\n\nOpen [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)\n\n## How to add accounts\n\n1. Log into Codex CLI with your ChatGPT account:\n   ```bash\n   codex login\n   ```\n2. Copy the generated auth file:\n   ```bash\n   cp ~/.codex/auth.json ~/Desktop/openai-accounts/acc1.json\n   ```\n3. In the Dashboard, click **+ Add Account** and enter the path to your auth file (e.g. `~/Desktop/openai-accounts/acc1.json`)\n\nRepeat for each account.\n\n## Auto-rotation\n\nEnable **Auto-rotation** in the right sidebar. The system will:\n\n| 5h Usage | Check Interval |\n|---|---|\n| < 50% | Every 30 minutes |\n| 50–80% | Every 10 minutes |\n| > 80% | Every 5 minutes |\n| **> 90%** | **Switch immediately** |\n\nSwitch events are logged in the Dashboard activity feed.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Auth files contain OAuth tokens — keep them secure and do not commit them to version control\n- Each usage check consumes a small number of Codex tokens (rounds to ~0% of the 5h window)\n- The auto-rotation only activates when the **Auto-rotation** toggle is enabled\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n\n\n\n## Screenshots\n\n部署界面预览：\n\n![Deploy 1](assets/deploy-1.jpg)\n![Deploy 2](assets/deploy-2.jpg)\n![Deploy 3](assets/deploy-3.jpg)\n\n## 更新动态\n\n我会持续更新，感兴趣可以关注我的抖音：\n\n![Douyin](assets/douyin.jpg)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":527,"aggregated":"# Codex Account Manager\n\nA dashboard for managing multiple OpenAI Codex accounts (ChatGPT OAuth), with real-time usage monitoring and automatic account rotation.\n> 原则上也可用于 Gemini / Claude 等账号管理，但我主要用 Codex，所以示例与实现以 Codex 为主。\n\n\n![Dashboard Preview](public/preview.png)\n\n## Features\n\n- **Multi-account management** — Add and switch between multiple OpenAI Codex accounts using ChatGPT OAuth tokens\n- **Real-time usage monitoring** — Shows 5-hour window and weekly quota usage by calling the Codex API directly\n- **Auto-rotation** — Automatically switches to the next account when the 5-hour usage exceeds 90%\n- **Smart polling** — Adjusts check frequency based on usage level (30min → 10min → 5min as usage increases)\n- **Auth file switching** — Copies the selected account's `auth.json` to `~/.codex/auth.json` on activation\n- **Token info** — Displays email, plan type, and token expiry decoded from JWT\n- **Activity logs** — Real-time log feed with rotation events and usage checks\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Frontend**: React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui\n- **Backend**: Express.js + Node.js\n- **Database**: MySQL (via XAMPP)\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Node.js 18+\n- MySQL (XAMPP recommended on macOS)\n- OpenAI Codex CLI installed (`npm install -g @openai/codex`)\n- ChatGPT Plus / Team / Pro account with Codex access\n\n## Setup\n\n### 1. Clone the repo\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/codex-account-manager.git\ncd codex-account-manager\n```\n\n### 2. Install dependencies\n\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n\n### 3. Configure environment\n\n```bash\ncp .env.example .env\n```\n\nEdit `.env` with your database credentials:\n\n```env\nPORT=3001\nFRONTEND_ORIGIN=http://localhost:8080\nDB_HOST=127.0.0.1\nDB_PORT=3306\nDB_SOCKET=/Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/var/mysql/mysql.sock\nDB_USER=root\nDB_PASSWORD=\nDB_NAME=codex_pool_manager\nVITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001\n```\n\n### 4. Create the database\n\nStart MySQL, then create a database named `codex_pool_manager`. The server will auto-create all tables on first run.\n\n### 5. Start the app\n\n```bash\n# Start backend\nnode server/index.js\n\n# Start frontend (in another terminal)\nnpm run dev\n```\n\nOpen [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)\n\n## How to add accounts\n\n1. Log into Codex CLI with your ChatGPT account:\n   ```bash\n   codex login\n   ```\n2. Copy the generated auth file:\n   ```bash\n   cp ~/.codex/auth.json ~/Desktop/openai-accounts/acc1.json\n   ```\n3. In the Dashboard, click **+ Add Account** and enter the path to your auth file (e.g. `~/Desktop/openai-accounts/acc1.json`)\n\nRepeat for each account.\n\n## Auto-rotation\n\nEnable **Auto-rotation** in the right sidebar. The system will:\n\n| 5h Usage | Check Interval |\n|---|---|\n| < 50% | Every 30 minutes |\n| 50–80% | Every 10 minutes |\n| > 80% | Every 5 minutes |\n| **> 90%** | **Switch immediately** |\n\nSwitch events are logged in the Dashboard activity feed.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Auth files contain OAuth tokens — keep them secure and do not commit them to version control\n- Each usage check consumes a small number of Codex tokens (rounds to ~0% of the 5h window)\n- The auto-rotation only activates when the **Auto-rotation** toggle is enabled\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n\n\n\n## Screenshots\n\n部署界面预览：\n\n![Deploy 1](assets/deploy-1.jpg)\n![Deploy 2](assets/deploy-2.jpg)\n![Deploy 3](assets/deploy-3.jpg)\n\n## 更新动态\n\n我会持续更新，感兴趣可以关注我的抖音：\n\n![Douyin](assets/douyin.jpg)","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774106983874}}
{"type":"message","id":"535d4323","parentId":"62ce0ea5","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:29:44.438Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_or232yjqrg78_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":".env.example file\n.gitignore file\nLICENSE file\nREADME.md file\nassets dir\nbun.lock file\nbun.lockb file\ncomponents.json file\neslint.config.js file\nindex.html file\npackage-lock.json file\npackage.json file\nplaywright-fixture.ts file\nplaywright.config.ts file\npostcss.config.js file\npublic dir\nserver dir\nsrc dir\ntailwind.config.ts file\ntsconfig.app.json file\ntsconfig.json file\ntsconfig.node.json file\nvite.config.ts file\nvitest.config.ts file"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1065,"aggregated":".env.example file\n.gitignore file\nLICENSE file\nREADME.md file\nassets dir\nbun.lock file\nbun.lockb file\ncomponents.json file\neslint.config.js file\nindex.html file\npackage-lock.json file\npackage.json file\nplaywright-fixture.ts file\nplaywright.config.ts file\npostcss.config.js file\npublic dir\nserver dir\nsrc dir\ntailwind.config.ts file\ntsconfig.app.json file\ntsconfig.json file\ntsconfig.node.json file\nvite.config.ts file\nvitest.config.ts file","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774106984413}}
{"type":"message","id":"0a26bd93","parentId":"535d4323","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:29:58.739Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full README. Let me summarize how to use this CodexPool repository for the user.","thinkingSignature":"f6f0c915fbd3df8585b4b9adee469bd077faa78c191d6fdd9ddcb75c52804cb8"},{"type":"text","text":"### CodexPool 使用指南\n\n**功能：** Codex 多账号管理面板（ChatGPT OAuth 账号）\n\n---\n\n#### 如何添加账号\n\n1. **先用 Codex CLI 登录账号**\n   ```bash\n   codex login\n   ```\n2. **复制 auth 文件到安全目录**\n   ```bash\n   cp ~/.codex/auth.json ~/Desktop/openai-accounts/acc1.json\n   ```\n3. **在 Dashboard（http://localhost:8080）右侧边栏点 `+ Add Account`**，输入 auth 文件路径\n\n每个账号重复以上步骤。\n\n---\n\n#### 自动切换规则\n\n开启右侧边栏的 **Auto-rotation** 后：\n\n| 5小时用量 | 检测频率 |\n|---------|---------|\n| < 50% | 每30分钟 |\n| 50-80% | 每10分钟 |\n| > 80% | 每5分钟 |\n| **> 90%** | **立即切换** |\n\n---\n\n#### 当前服务状态\n\n| 服务 | 地址 | 状态 |\n|------|------|------|\n| 前端 | http://localhost:8080 | ✅ 运行中 |\n| 后端 | http://localhost:3001 | ✅ 运行中 |\n\n---\n\n#### 注意事项\n\n- auth 文件含 OAuth 凭据，**不要提交到 Git**\n- 每次用量检测消耗少量 Codex token（可忽略）\n- 自动切换需要开启右侧 `Auto-rotation` 开关"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100749,"output":313,"cacheRead":37752,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138814,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774106984440}}
{"type":"message","id":"f63cc8db","parentId":"0a26bd93","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:31:38.387Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-21 23:31:37 GMT+8] Feishu[feishu-assistant] DM | ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7 [msg:om_x100b54dfd359bca0c32ae5bab628649]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54dfd359bca0c32ae5bab628649\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 23:31 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\"\n}\n```\n\n如果我没有codex cli账号，是不是就无法使用codexpool了？"}],"timestamp":1774107098383}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ef73672","parentId":"f63cc8db","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:31:56.965Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if they need a Codex CLI account to use CodexPool. Let me think about this.\n\nCodexPool is a dashboard for managing multiple Codex accounts. Looking at the README:\n- It uses OpenAI Codex accounts (ChatGPT OAuth)\n- Auth files (`~/.codex/auth.json`) are used\n- The auto-rotation copies auth files to `~/.codex/auth.json`\n\nSo yes, you need actual Codex accounts to use this. But wait - does CodexPool itself require Codex CLI to be installed? The README says:\n- OpenAI Codex CLI installed (`npm install -g @openai/codex`)\n\n\n- ChatGPT Plus/Team/Pro account with Codex access\n\nCodexPool is just the dashboard - it manages the auth files and monitors usage, but the actual Codex CLI does the work. So the user needs a Codex CLI account with Plus/Team/Pro subscription, though the CodexPool dashboard itself is just a management tool, not the actual CLI. I should ask what they're trying to accomplish to give better guidance.","thinkingSignature":"dd9de5a4fed4e23a03e4ec1914d585b7f5a75b2238048b79bcb554c1d4737191"},{"type":"text","text":"是的，**需要真实 Codex 账号**才能用 CodexPool。\n\nCodexPool 本质上是一个**管理面板**，它的工作是：\n- 存储多个 `auth.json`（OAuth 凭据文件）\n- 监控各账号用量\n- 自动切换到用量低的账号\n\n但**实际调用 Codex API 执行任务**，还是靠本地的 Codex CLI。\n\n---\n\n#### 所以你需要：\n\n1. **ChatGPT Plus / Team / Pro 账号**（开通了 Codex 权限）\n2. **本地安装 Codex CLI**：\n   ```bash\n   npm install -g @openai/codex\n   ```\n3. **用 `codex login` 登录**生成 `auth.json`\n4. CodexPool 帮你**管理多个账号**的 auth 文件和用量切换\n\n---\n\n#### 如果你只是需要一个通用的 AI 编程 Agent\n\n不一定需要 Codex。可以直接用：\n- **Claude Code**（claude.ai/code）\n- **Cursor**（cursor.com）\n- **GitHub Copilot**\n\n这些都有各自的账号体系，不需要额外的多账号管理面板。\n\n---\n\n你具体想解决什么问题？是想用 Codex 还是只是想找一个好用的编程 Agent？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":125,"output":453,"cacheRead":136993,"cacheWrite":1969,"totalTokens":139540,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774107098386}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab88b6fb","parentId":"3ef73672","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:32:31.799Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-21 23:32:31 GMT+8] Feishu[feishu-assistant] DM | ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7 [msg:om_x100b54dfee24e0a4c3b9a342500e197]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54dfee24e0a4c3b9a342500e197\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 23:32 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\"\n}\n```\n\n我是通过中转站来使用codex的，可以使用codexpool吗"}],"timestamp":1774107151795}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd1f666b","parentId":"ab88b6fb","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:32:45.924Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is using Codex through a proxy/translation layer (中转站), not through the official Codex CLI. Let me think about this.\n\nCodexPool was designed specifically for managing ChatGPT OAuth auth files (auth.json) from the official Codex CLI. It copies auth files to ~/.codex/auth.json for the CLI to use. If the user is using a proxy/relay service, their authentication mechanism would be completely different - likely an API key or a custom auth setup, not the official Codex CLI auth flow.\n\nCodexPool wouldn't work with a proxy setup because:\n1. It manages Codex CLI auth files, not API keys\n2. It expects the Codex CLI to be installed and managing auth locally\n\n\n3. A relay service would bypass the CLI entirely, using the API directly instead\n\nSo unless the proxy supports the same auth.json format that CodexPool generates, there's no straightforward way to integrate them.","thinkingSignature":"ae9211d296955734fa7d7e7380f32063a474b62d9679408870936c9ec91ebe72"},{"type":"text","text":"这个有兼容性问题。\n\n**CodexPool 依赖的是 Codex CLI 的 `auth.json` 文件**（OAuth 格式），但中转站通常用的是：\n- API Key（直接调 OpenAI/微软接口）\n- 自定义 Token\n\n两者机制完全不同，CodexPool **无法直接管理中转站的账号**。\n\n---\n\n#### 你的实际情况\n\n如果你用中转站，**CodexPool 对你没用**，可以关掉节省资源。\n\n真正需要的是：\n- **API Key 管理** → 存到环境变量或配置文件\n- **用量监控** → 中转站后台一般自带\n- **自动切换** → 中转站自己处理，不归你管\n\n---\n\n#### 建议\n\n如果你想继续用 CodexPool，需要：\n1. 了解你的中转站是否支持导出/同步官方 Codex OAuth 格式\n2. 或者放弃 CodexPool，改用简单的 Key 管理方案\n\n**你用的是什么中转站？** 告诉我名称，我帮你看有没有更好的方案。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":125,"output":394,"cacheRead":138694,"cacheWrite":834,"totalTokens":140047,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774107151798}}
{"type":"message","id":"36227d09","parentId":"fd1f666b","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:52:34.481Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-21 23:52:33 GMT+8] Feishu[feishu-assistant] DM | ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7 [msg:om_x100b54dfa2de60a0c34db04472d422c]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54dfa2de60a0c34db04472d422c\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-21 23:52 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\"\n}\n```\n\n怎么免费获得gpt的team号呢"}],"timestamp":1774108354477}}
{"type":"message","id":"854973ed","parentId":"36227d09","timestamp":"2026-03-21T15:52:54.768Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking how to get a free GPT Team account. This is a question about getting OpenAI's ChatGPT Team plan for free. I should provide honest, practical advice about legitimate ways to get access without doing anything illegal or violating terms of service.\n\nLet me think about legitimate ways:\n1. OpenAI occasionally gives free access to Team through promotions\n2. Some research programs or beta access\n3. Work/company-provided accounts\n4. Educational discounts\n5. Wait for promotional periods\n\nI should be straightforward and not suggest anything fraudulent.","thinkingSignature":"afa294c1d6df8b4723d53810b1ab5c8f06708dad1578b0b9cac3aa473ada41d9"},{"type":"text","text":"这个问题比较实际。几个**合法途径**：\n\n#### 1. 官方免费试用\nOpenAI 偶尔会放出 Team/Plus 的限时免费试用，关注他们的官网或 X（@OpenAI）公告。\n\n#### 2. 公司/团队账号\n如果你有公司或工作室，可以申请 OpenAI Enterprise/Team，团队分摊费用后每人成本不高。\n\n#### 3. 开发者计划\nOpenAI 有一些开发者加速计划，符合条件可能获得 API 额度或产品试用。\n\n#### 4. 教育/研究用途\n学生或研究人员可以通过 OpenAI Education programs 申请。\n\n---\n\n⚠️ **不建议**去找所谓\"免费账号\"渠道——这类基本是：\n- 共享账号（隐私泄露风险）\n- 盗刷信用卡（违法）\n- 钓鱼陷阱\n\n**真实成本：** ChatGPT Team 每月约 $30/人，5人团每人 $6/月，是最便宜的官方方案。\n\n---\n\n你主要是想用 Codex 还是 ChatGPT？不同用途有不同的性价比方案。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":125,"output":320,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":140055,"totalTokens":140500,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774108354480}}
